Service
kafka-bootstrap 
is a Kubernetes Service that acts as the entry point for clients (applications) to connect to your Kafka cluster(kafka-bootstrap:9092).
Think of Kafka cluster like a group of servers (brokers):
You don’t want your app to connect to each broker manually ❌
Instead, you give one address → that’s kafka-bootstrap ✅
👉 It works like a “entry point” to Kafka.
What Exactly It Does
It is usually a ClusterIP service
It points to all Kafka brokers (pods)
It provides a single DNS name
Example:
kafka-bootstrap.default.svc.cluster.local:9092
Your app connects to this 👆
How It Works Internally
Your app connects to kafka-bootstrap
Kafka returns metadata (list of all brokers)
After that:
Producer/Consumer directly talks to correct broker
👉 So bootstrap is only for initial connection, not full traffic
